The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                               NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Chennai, July 11 (PTI): The Tamil Nadu government has told Madras High Court it would file an appeal against the plea of Nalini, a life convict in the Rajiv Gandhi assassination case, seeking premature release.           
	The state made this submission before the court, which reserved orders on a petition filed by Janata Party chief Subramanian Swamy seeking to implead himself in Nalinis plea. Swamys counsel said he feared the Centre and the state may collude with Nalini and take a legally biased stand in the case.                  
	 London (PTI): Britain has decided to allow Indian professionals, who did not qualify under its new immigration rules, to return and resume work. It has decided to compensate them for financial losses.                  
	 Kathmandu (PTI): The final hearing on Bikini Killer Charles Sobhrajs plea, challenging his life sentence for murdering an American tourist, has been deferred till August 10 by Nepals Supreme Court.                   
	 Bhopal (PTI): The Madhya Pradesh government has decided to set up a call centre to address peoples grievances. Under the e-governance programme, 9,232 common service centres would be established in five villages. A state-level call centre will be set up by August 15, an official said. These centres will be connected by the state wide-area network. Many online assistance schemes have been introduced.                   
	 Jammu (PTI): Four persons, who allegedly threw the body of a slain horse into a temple in Rajouri district on Thursday were arrested on Friday. The mischief-makers intention was to trigger communal clashes, police said. A bandh has been called in protest against the desecration.                   
	 Jammu (PTI): A godman was arrested for allegedly raping a woman in Rajouri district on Friday, police said. The 26-year-old victim alleged that she had been lured under the pretext that the accused would bless her with a male child.
                                                                                                                         
